node.text: This is the Earthship Biotecture in Taos, New Mexico and this is what it’s like to stay in a home that’s built from trash, creates its own heat, energy, and collects water from the rain to recycle 4 times! True #greenliving #offthegrid #offthegridliving featuring @earthship @ecolivingmatrix

node.title: Living off the grid in a desert Earthship

Have you heard about the opportunity to win a flight to Hawai'i? ICYMI, I've partnered with @HawaiianAirlines and @Mastercard for their #alohafromabove sweepstakes! This week, we’re taking the virtual scavenger hunt to the island of Moloka'i! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I’ve been to every visitable island in Hawai'i, and I loved Moloka'i for the lush jungles, enchanting waterfalls, beautiful valleys and wild beaches. Wishing for a chance to visit? The locations are hidden all around the island, and your scavenger hunt clues are in this video. #Ad ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
So, here's how it works. Just go to AlohaFromAboveSweepstakes.com (link in bio) and search for five hidden letters, A-L-O-H-A, within a map of Moloka'i. Once you find all the letters, you can enter the sweepstakes for a chance to win a flight to Hawai'i. There's a new chance to win next week, too, with clues on @hawaiianairlines! ⁣
⁣
(No purc nec; open to 50 US/DC, terr, 18+/age of maj; ends 1/24/21.) #sweepstakes

node.text:
Here’s a chance to win a flight to Hawai'i! Hawai'i has captured my heart ever since childhood when I'd go visit my family there. Each island is so different with unique adventures of the aquatic, jungly, and oftentimes rocky kind! Have you been before or are you itching to go? Today I'm reminiscing about Lānaʻi one of the least-visited and most adventurous islands. The diving is great, the sunsets are magical, and I loved the sense of solitude there. ⁣
⁣
I've partnered with @HawaiianAirlines and @Mastercard for their #AlohaFromAbove sweepstakes! The locations are hidden all around the island, and your scavenger hunt clues are in this video. #Ad ⁣
⁣
So, here's how it works. Just go to AlohaFromAboveSweepstakes.com (link in bio) and search for five hidden letters, A-L-O-H-A, within a map of Lānaʻi. Once you find all the letters, enter the sweepstakes for a chance to win a flight to Hawai'i. Come back each week for a new chance to win! ⁣
⁣
(No purc nec; open to 50 US/DC, terr, 18+/age of maj; ends 1/24/21.) #Sweepstakes

node.text:
Wait for it... 🐦 ⁣
⁣
People have been telling me about the famous Chickadee Ridge in Tahoe and it was so cool to finally check it out! I brought along my niece and the hand sani. ⁣
⁣
So frankly before the ‘Rona I rarely traveled with hand sanitizer and it wasn’t until lately that I started looking into it more. There are times when running water just isn’t available and lots of places ask us to sanitize before entering their establishments now, too!
⁣
But that doesn’t mean I want chemicals and harsh perfumes on my skin. You too? We can all stop looking because I found the answer! @ecofreaks_usa has hand sanitizer that is unscented, leaves no residue, and is free from phthalates, parabens, and perfumes. Now if I enter an establishment and they want me to use hand sani, I’ve got my own!⁣
⁣
The company has also planted over 2k trees with One Tree Planted, are a WWF partner in conservation, and they offer large refills to cut down on single use plastics. If you dig that too you can get a discount on their website (link in bio) with the code TRAVEL20. Happy (cleaner) trails! #bringyourfreak #sponsored

node.text:
Baby blue water and white sand. #ad This is one of many perfect beaches in Aruba. And I love the contrast here. On one side of the island it’s rugged, 4 x 4 territory and on the other it’s white sand beaches and that perfect Caribbean blue water. ⁣
⁣
The last two times I visited I stayed in Palm Beach, where most of the high-rise hotels are. But this time I really wanted a smaller, boutique experience and Manchebo beach was perfect. No crowds, just perfectly quiet beach days. 

The Manchebo Resort and Spa was perfect - with a truly amazing spa! I also love that they use paper straws and check out all those solar panels! #onehappyisland

node.text:
Just keep on looping and feel the calm wash over you,🎶 on. 
This is in the far north of Manitoba, at the literal end of the road. While Gillam is more of an industrial town with only a few hundred (very friendly) residents, it’s certainly not set up for tourism. Yet it ended up being the perfect place to find solitude and capture the Aurora Borealis. What started out as an unintended layover when our flight to Churchhill was canceled due to weather became a northern light wonderland. This illustrates so well what I love about the far north - the peace and quiet, the perfectly cold evenings with clear skies, the little snow foxes scurrying by, and the incredible Aurora dancing 💃🏼 #exploreMB

node.text: The ocean I grew up knowing was cold and dark, with big waves and strong undertow. As a kid I didn’t care. Swimming took precedence over everything else. I don’t know where that innate love of water came from, but I’m so damn grateful. It made me care about the planet, the animals, and keeping it all clean. now I realize the ocean can be clear and so full of visible life! In the Galapagos, swimming with penguins, sea lions, schools of eagle rays, and even hammerheads, with just a mask and snorkel, - no tank needed - blew my mind. I’ve never seen such abundance under the water. People told me that the snorkeling could be even better than the scuba in the Galapagos and I totally believe them now (catch @jfur07 on the cover and at the end with the sea lions!) what an amazing week of sailing with @andando_tours.

node.text:
I'll never forget the first time I saw the Milky Way. Growing up in greater LA, it's just not something you see much unless you go out into nature. As an adult, I plan trips around the moon cycles so that I can see this dazzling display. Bonus points when a bunch of meteor showers converge, as you'll see in the timelapse. ...
As anyone who is into astrophotography knows, the more you get into it the more you plan it out so that you can get the Milky Way in the right moment, facing the right direction. That often means going to greater lengths, like a night hike miles down to a lake in a dark sky park, to see it. No regrets. This was a beautiful #MontanaMoment to capture @VisitMontana #sponsored

node.text:
Who else looks forward to winter??⁣
⁣
Maybe because it is still new to me or because the winters here are mild, I just get so excited every time it snows. I still text pictures to my mom every time. But one thing I haven’t figured out how to do is drive in it. I will honestly wait until it’s done and has melted a bit and then I will emerge and buy groceries 🤣 (places in order: Davos, Switzerland, Denali, Alaska, Tahoe, Nevada, Eastern Sierras, California, and Gillam, Manitoba)

node.text:
An ode to snowy places I’ve loved before. ⁣
⁣
It’s looking like we are getting a white Christmas here in the eastern Sierras! Since I grew up in greater LA, this will only be the third I’ve ever had so I’m beyond excited! Tell me what you guys are doing for the holidays? Distract me from the craziness in the world pretty please 🙏🏻 ⁣
⁣
#idaho #visitidaho #idahoexplored @visitidaho #outdooradventures #shetravels #winterwonderland

node.text:
Loving this trend. What makes you feel like a woman?⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I feel like we can be, and are pretty much expected to be, so many things rolled up into one pretty package.⁣
⁣
I definitely feel pressure to be perfect. I feel expectations. I never want to say the wrong thing or be perceived the wrong way. But I’m reminded that there are so many different facets of me and so many parts that I can put forward. If someone judges one part of me, they’ve limited their potential to get to know all parts of me, and isn’t that unfortunate? #iamwoman #solotraveler #solofemaletraveler #girlpower #girlpowertravel

node.text:
I was SO scared to travel by myself the first time, it took me a year to build up to the idea. But then it turned out better than I could have EVER imagined. ⁣
⁣
Over the years women have reached out to me to tell me that they, too, how beautiful experiences. You never know who you’ll meet - with the most important of all, the real you. ⁣
⁣
Don’t worry about having everything figured out. Don’t feel like you have to know everything that will happen. That’s the beauty of it - the serendipity. ⁣
⁣
I can’t even count how many solo trips I’ve been on now, but sharing this footage from my most recent one to the Exumas in the Bahamas, a PERFECT place to go. I stayed on Staniel Cay where everyone waves and the whole island is family. Link in my bio today for some of the amazing things that I did there with @3nsstanielcay #solotravel #solofemaletraveler #bahamas #dametraveler #shetravels

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Kristin Addis on November 21, 2021 tagging @visitthebahamas, @embracestanielcay, and @3nsstanielcay. May be an image of body of water.

node.text:
My favorite photos from a week on Staniel Cay in the Bahamas, the kind of place where everyone waves and says hello, the seaside is abundant, and the water is sooo clear. ⁣
⁣
I explored it all with @3nsstanielcay and stayed at @embracestanielcay a #womanownedbusiness and #blackownedbusinesses by 2 tenacious boss ladies who built it from the ground up, without the benefit of bank loans.⁣
⁣
Shout out to Captain Dave too, who took the photo of me at the piano, diving down multiple times to get the shot! Talk about going the extra (nautical) mile! #bahamas #bahamasbound @visitthebahamas #underwaterlife

node.text:
Would you trust fall into a bunch of nurse sharks? 😜⁣
⁣
These guys are pretty tame, but even swimming with tiger sharks a few weeks ago did too. I’m coming to find them to be such beautiful creatures and thankful to @3nsstanielcay for the opportunity to see them and the sand bar (prev reel) AND swimming pigs (2 reels ago) in the same morning. ⁣
@visitthebahamas @embracestanielcay #exumas #sharkweek #bahamasbound #sharklover

node.text:
I appear and disappear with the tides, revealing new colors and shades of blue as I come and go…⁣
⁣
The colors in the Exumas are brilliant. The water is so clear and the sand so white. It was awesome being able to see it from above!⁣
⁣
This was one of the stops on my day tour with @3nsstanielcay between the swimming pigs (prev reel) and the nurse sharks (up next!). Was such an action packed day and I loved it all! #exumas #bahamas @visitthebahamas #fromwhereidrone #droneoftheday #dronepic

node.text:
When you finally meet your dream celebrities 🐷 ⁣
⁣
These swimming pigs were honestly delightful. The way that they swam and huffed and snorted was probably the cutest thing I’ve seen all year. I  could swim with them every day. An aquatic creature - who knew? Our captain, Dave with @3nsstanielcay was a champ, taking our boat to all the best stops and being a dedicated photographer for me. He was having just as much fun as I was. Don’t you love that? ⁣
⁣
#3nsstanielcay #exumabahamas #visitbahamas #stanielcay #oceanlovers

node.text:
I’m not a regular room I’m a cool room 😉 ⁣
⁣
It was my first time staying in a fancy overwater bungalow at @icfr_polynesia #icmoana and I didn’t even know there would be a coffee table that gave a view of the reef below! So fun, we took turns swimming underneath just cause we could. ⁣
⁣
Have you ever stayed in and overwater bungalow before? Do you want to? I can’t explain why, but it’s so cool just being able to walk straight out of your bedroom and into the ocean! ⁣
⁣
#borabora #hostedstay #frenchpolynesia #luxurytravel #honeymoondestination

node.text:
I don’t know how I could ever summarize nine beautiful weeks in what has become my most favorite place in the world - French Polynesia, but I’m going to try!⁣
⁣
Spanning 10 islands that each had their own special beauty, And spending one month just swimming with whales every day, as an ocean lover it’s hard to find a better place. We dove with humpbacks, tiger sharks, hundreds of reef sharks and even dolphins. The lagoons were glittering and beautiful, and the people so warm almost always with a wave and a hello.⁣
⁣
It’s also a place where you earn your travel. Logistics aren’t easy. I’ll always remember the time we took a tiny fishing boat across the ocean because planes can’t land on that little island when it rains. And yet what a wonderful memory. ⁣
⁣
I’ll miss eating raw, line-caught seafood every day. Will miss the smiles and 🤙🏻. Will tuck it thankfully in my heart knowing I’m coming back again. ⁣
⁣
So grateful to @tahititourismenorthamerica for helping with this journey. Check out their feed for some serious French Polynesia eye candy. #frenchpolynesia #dametraveler #tropicalvibes #lovetahiti some pics taken by @jfur07 my awesome travel buddy.

node.text:
Would you swim with Tiger sharks?
⁣
When I heard about @denistemae’s conservation work with the sharks and his long-standing relationship with them on Tikehau, I knew I had to see them with him. The first time i saw her I couldn’t believe how beautiful she was and all of my nervousness just became excitement. She was gentle and curious, and I’m still in awe of the experience of freediving with her.⁣
⁣
Spending the past week diving with her and hundreds of reef sharks, I know we’ve got it all wrong with how many get killed each year and how few actually attack, usually without meaning to. In 2020 there were 57 attacks yet 100 million sharks were killed, mostly for finning (shark fin soup). ⁣
⁣
Maybe this isn’t for everyone, but I hope we can agree they deserve respect and they’re an essential part of a healthy ocean and therefore, life. #frenchpolynesia #tahititourisme #sharkweek #sharkselfie #sharks #oceanlover
